Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Prime Minister Haider Al-Abadi of Iraq. They discussed the Trump Administration's commitment to protecting persecuted Christians and religious minorities in Iraq and the Middle East. They also talked about the upcoming elections in Iraq, reports of Iran trying to interfere in the election, and the need for free and fair elections that include displaced citizens. Pence congratulated Abadi on the successes of the Iraqi Security Forces against ISIS and highlighted the partnership between Iraq's Security Forces and the US military and coalition partners. They also discussed the reopening of the Iraqi Kurdistan Region's airports and the initial payment of some Kurdistan Regional Government salaries. Both leaders expressed their desire for increased trade and economic ties between Iraq and the United States.